content:
✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: I tried to solve it and I liked it. I hope others will like it as well.

It reminds me of another clash with the same ascii pattern and most people didn't manage to solve it.
(To be approved a clash to has be solved in less than 5 minutes)

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: I had fun searching for a solution. In the end i wrote a function "wrap" that gets called n times to create a section every loop. So i don't think that it will be hard to solve this clash.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: It took me some time to come up with a logical & short solution, but it was quite rewarding once I had it and I had fun while searching for it. So, nice clash!

Goal
* It's a rectangular target, and the shapes look more like "squares" than "circles" to me…?

* Please delete the example - the same has been shown in Example section.

Thanks.

Hi, 5DN1L... I'm sorry but I think that you're wrong to ask him to delete the example. When I made the first Test-Case in my contribution, It automatically became the Example. I don't think that you can get rid of the example... that's all I'm saying.
However I could be wrong.

Also, the author has already stated that the target consists of red and white "SQUARES" stacked onto each other, this would mean that it is a rectangular target. This means that your comment is slightly obvious... right? 

However I could be wrong again...

Yours apologetically, Code-Parser.
My comments were made 26 days ago. The author had followed up my comments before you read my comments.

Ok, I'm very sorry 5DN1L. Please ignore my previous comment. 
I misread...

Sorry, Code-Parser.
